DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Collects device information events for NetApp appliances.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: Command line input: the command is '(\S+)'\. The full command line is '(.+)'\.
(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: CIFS: Cifs ([-\w_ ]+) operation (0x[a-f\d]+) is not supported on the filer\. Requested by ([\d.]+)\((\S*)\)\..*

FastField.defaultValue: CIFS $6 operation requested by "$8" is not supported on the filer

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: CIFS: An oplock break request to station ([\d.]+)\((\S*)\) for filer (\S+), share (\S+), file (.+) has timed out\..*

FastField.defaultValue: CIFS oplock break request to "$6" has timed out

FastFormatter.format: Device: $3, Priority: $5, Filer: $8, Share: $9, File: "$10", Host: $7

FastFormatter.condition: \d{1,2}:\d{2}[ap]m (.+?),? \d+ NFS ops, \d+ CIFS ops, \d+ HTTP ops, \d+ FCP ops, \d+ iSCSI ops.*
(\d{1,2}:\d{2}[ap]m) .+,? (\d+) NFS ops, (\d+) CIFS ops, (\d+) HTTP ops, (\d+) FCP ops, (\d+) iSCSI ops.*
FastFormatter.format: Time: $8, Op Count: "NFS $9, CIFS $10, HTTP $11, FCP $12, iSCSI $13"

FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?wafl.scan.start:\w+]: Starting WAFL layout measurement on volume [-\w:_]+\.
\[\S+: ?wafl.reallocate.check.under:\w+]: Allocation check on '[^']+' is \d+, \(threshold \d+\), so not reallocating\.
\[\S+: ?wafl.reallocate.check.highAdvise:\w+]: Allocation check on '[^']+' is \d+, hotspot \d+ \(threshold \d+\), consider running reallocate\.
\[\S+: ?wafl.vol.autoSize.fail:\w+]: Unable to grow volume '[^']+' to recover space:

FastFormatter.condition: Time server '(.+)' is not responding to time synchronization requests
FastFormatter.format: Time server "$8" is not responding to time synchronization requests

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: SIS change logging metafile for volume ([-@/\w:_]+) is full.*
FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?sis.changelog.full:\w+]: SIS change logging metafile for volume [-@/\w:_]+ is full\.

FastField.defaultValue: SIS change logging metafile for volume "$6" is full
SIS change logging metafile for volume "$6" is full

FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?sis.autoSched.failed:\w+]: SIS operation for [-@/\w:_]+ could not be auto scheduled:

FastField.defaultValue: SIS change logging metafile for volume "$6" is full
SIS change logging metafile for volume "$6" is full

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: SnapMirror source volume ([-\w:_]+) has no new data for ([-\w:_]+).*
FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?snapmirror.src.noNewData:\w+]: SnapMirror source volume [-\w:_]+ has no new data for [-\w:_]+

FastField.defaultValue: SnapMirror source volume "$6" has no new data for $7
SnapMirror source volume "$6" has no new data for $7

FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?snapmirror.dst.updateDelayed:\w+]: Transfer from [-\w:_]+ to [-\w:_]+ is in progress, SnapMirror transfer from [-\w:_]+ delayed\.

FastField.defaultValue: Transfer from "$6" to "$7" is in progress

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([-\w.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: CIFS: Cifs operation (0x[a-f\d]+) is not supported on the filer\. Request information: (0x[a-f\d]+) ([^(]+)\((\S*)\)\..*

FastField.defaultValue: CIFS operation requested by "$8" is not supported on the filer

FastPattern.pattern: \[\S+: ?app.log.info:\w+]: ?\w+: [-\w.: ()]+: Scanning datastores with the following morefs: \[.+\]
\[\S+: ?callhome.hm.sas.alert.major:\w+]: Call home for SAS Connectivity Monitor: [-\w_]+\[.+\]
\[\S+: ?openssh.versionExchange.Fail:\w+]: Did not receive identification string from [\d.]+
\[\S+: ?net.if.filterDrop:\w+\]: ?Protocol Filter: '\d+' '[^']+' packets were dropped by the per-interface protocol

\[\S+: ?zapi.snapshot.success:\w+]: Asynchronous creation of Snapshot copy named [-\w:_]+ in volume [-\w:_]+ was successful\. The Snapshot copy was created \d+ milliseconds after the request was received by ZAPI.
\[\S+: ?cf.hwassist.socBindFailed:\w+\]: ?hw_assist: bind failed to port \d+ on IP address [-\w.]+\. Error \d+

FastPattern.matcher: (\d+) ([\d.]+) \[(\S+): ?([\w.]+):(\w+)]: ([\w ]+)\. The client IP address:port is ([-\w.]+):(\d+)\. The local IP address:port is ([-\w.]+):(\d+)\. The protocol requesting the operation is (\S+)\. The RPC Program Number for the operation is (\d+)\. The RPC Procedure Number for the operation is (\d+)\. The disk process UUID is (\S+)\..* The Vserver identifier is (\d+).
